@page "/"

<PageTitle>Wikidown</PageTitle>

<div class="hero">
    <h1>Wikidown</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        An Azure-DevOps-Wiki-compatible wiki that lives in <code>/docs</code> of your
        code repo. Edit in the browser, commit straight to GitHub or Azure DevOps.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="connect">Open a wiki</a>
    </p>
</div>

<h2>How it works</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Sign in with GitHub Device Flow or paste a PAT for GitHub / Azure DevOps.</li>
    <li>Pick the repo (and branch) that holds your <code>/docs</code> folder.</li>
    <li>Browse, edit, and save pages — the app commits via REST.</li>
</ol>

<p class="text-muted small">
    Your token stays in the browser. No backend; everything runs client-side.
</p>
